Somewhere, there is a horse.
A horse with no skin.
Every day, the fierce wind lashes against his exposed flesh, flaying it with leaves, coating it in dust, drying it to a crackling, all-over-body scab.
But he is not sad.
Oh no, this horse is proud.
Because he knows that somewhere, his skin was made into a kick-ass work of Commander Keen fan art.
